// ch05 §5.12: "A by-reference capture (`[&x]`) is a reference-typed
// member ... the closure value itself becomes a lifetime-tracked value."
// Mutating through the closure is visible through the original variable
// name afterward, exactly like writing through any other `T&` (ch03).
// `f`'s last use is the call itself, so reading `x` directly afterward
// is fine (mirrors `borrow_released_after_last_use_permits_direct_write`
// in 04_references_borrow).
int main() {
    int x = 5;
    auto f = [&x]() { x = 10; return x; };
    int y = f();
    return x + y;
}
